  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Legal Aid to refugees in Greece ( Lesbos)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GCR has been monitoring the situation in Lesvos since February 2015 with periodic reports and has established a permanent presence on the island since the spring of 2016, with the support and in partnership with Oxfam. The overall objective of this particular intervention is the strengthening of the provision of legal services to persons in need of international protection in Lesvos, with a focus on vulnerable women and children, including UAMs. The project will operate across the different safe spaces that exist in the island, which are currently providing tailored support and activities for vulnerable women and children. The project design proposed, involves a small team of 1 asylum lawyer, 1 interpreter and/or 1 social worker who will be visiting the afore -mentioned locations on a biweekly basis in order to provide legal information, counsel, assistance and representation in all appropriate cases. The team will also be taking up referrals by other GCR lawyers present in the island and by other partner organizations that provide services to such vulnerable groups.</narrative>
  </description>
